name: CNN
text: Amazon has labeled more than 25,000 of its products as "Climate Pledge Friendly," indicating that each of those products aligns with Amazon's "Climate Pledge," a commitment to having a net-zero carbon footprint by 2040 https://t.co/ApCK3StgUN

name: CNN
text: An ordinary workday quickly turned into a rescue mission after a bridge inspector spotted a stranded dog 120 feet above the Mississippi River https://t.co/tmjiJrJBU7

name: CNN
text:
Breonna Taylor's case has spurred protests and placed a greater focus on how policing impacts Black women.

Locally, her death led to the passage of "Breonna's Law," banning no-knock warrants, and the hiring of a new interim Louisville police chief. https://t.co/aRg7HnWRPN

name: CNN
text: The Metropolitan Opera has announced that it's canceling its entire season due to the pandemic. "We have to wait for an effective vaccine to be widely available and that's not likely going to happen until summer," General Manager Peter Gelb said in a video https://t.co/K2nKymKAo1

name: CNN
text:
President Trump gave a speech in Ohio on Monday that included some important false and misleading claims about jobs.

Trump claimed that "we brought back 700,000" manufacturing jobs

Facts First: This was not even true before the pandemic-driven recession https://t.co/C7mpYZAgxu

name: CNN
text: Excess belly fat is associated with a higher risk of early death from any cause, regardless of how much overall body fat you have, a new study finds https://t.co/X4sbbgXfAE

name: CNN
text: The British government is exploring the possibility of clinical trials in which volunteers are deliberately exposed to coronavirus to test the effectiveness of vaccine candidates, the UK Department for Business, Energy, and Industrial Strategy has revealed https://t.co/nveDd4cGYB

name: CNN
text: Deliberately infecting study participants poses more risks and raises ethical concerns compared to randomized controlled trials, where study subjects receive a vaccine or a placebo, and researchers monitor to see if they become ill afterward. https://t.co/znvp8ArWds

name: CNN
text: Event organizers for the annual Times Square New Year’s Eve celebration have announced that the countdown will take place this year, albeit with some changes in format https://t.co/RHfY8s7Yjz

name: CNN
text: Facebook has allowed political advertisers to target hundreds of misleading ads about Joe Biden and the USPS to swing-state voters in recent weeks, in an apparent failure to enforce its own platform rules less than two months before Election Day https://t.co/OV1KN7dhGl

name: CNN
text: Protests intensify on the streets of Louisville after one of the three officers involved in Breonna Taylor's case was indicted on first-degree wanton endangerment charges; no officers were charged directly with Taylor's death. https://t.co/E8JCc6hQbS https://t.co/UgmMWwYPLT

name: CNN
text: While attempting to administer a shot to Tyrod Taylor's ribs, a Los Angeles Chargers team doctor accidentally punctured one of the quarterback's lungs instead https://t.co/CJaODda1ve

name: CNN
text: More than 587,000 children in the United States have tested positive for Covid-19 since the beginning of the coronavirus pandemic earlier this year, according to the American Academy of Pediatrics and the Children’s Hospital Association https://t.co/7hmIpvO7Mg

name: CNN
text: Two officers with the Louisville Metro Police Department were shot Wednesday night during protests following a grand jury decision in the Breonna Taylor case, the interim chief of the Louisville Police Department confirmed in a press briefing https://t.co/3dEIyRX0DK

name: CNN
text: Florida's attorney general has requested that the FBI and the Florida Department of Law Enforcement investigate Michael Bloomberg's efforts to reinstate the voting rights of felons by paying their fees, according to a letter to the agencies provided to CNN https://t.co/PMSz1Oo9by

name: CNN
text: Fact check: President Trump made false claims about his record on manufacturing and coal jobs during a speech in Ohio on Monday https://t.co/BjtyFgw6Ju

name: CNN
text:
A mini-moon is on track to enter Earth's orbit and come as close as 27,000 miles away.

However, rather than some asteroid that will orbit around the Earth, it may actually just be some old space junk that made its way back to our planet. https://t.co/3O5qJh47Bt
